{
  "texts": [
    "In detail, information about electricity price and building total electrical consumption is provided as input to the RBC strategy managing the BESS.",
    "The updated BESS SOC value is obtained from the BESS model, which receives directives regarding whether to charge or discharge the battery.",
    "Then, BESS SOC, PV electricity production and electricity price are additionally relayed as state variables.",
    "These variables are used by DRL controller or RBC to determine the cooling mode and the cooling fraction during each control time step.",
    "To conclude, the controller learns the optimal control strategy through the assessment of a reward function, formulated as a function of the analysed scenario (e.g., inductive or transductive TL)."
  ]
}